## PermissionResolverService

Her auth request'te permission set Redis'ten çekilir. Cache miss → DB'den resolve + cache'e yaz:

```typescript
@Injectable()
export class PermissionResolverService {
  constructor(
    private readonly prisma: PrismaService,
    private readonly redis: RedisService,
    private readonly attributeRuleEvaluator: AttributeRuleEvaluatorService,
  ) {}

  async getUserPermissions(userId: string): Promise<Set<Permission>> {
    const cacheKey = `user_permissions:${userId}`;
    const cached = await this.redis.get(cacheKey);
    if (cached) return new Set(JSON.parse(cached));

    const permissions = await this.resolveFromDb(userId);
    await this.redis.setex(cacheKey, 300, JSON.stringify([...permissions]));
    return permissions;
  }

  private async resolveFromDb(userId: string): Promise<Set<Permission>> {
    // 1. Direct role assignments
    const directAssignments = await this.prisma.user_roles.findMany({
      where: { user_id: userId, source: 'DIRECT' },
      include: { role: { include: { role_permissions: true } } },
    });

    // 2. Attribute rule matches
    const user = await this.prisma.users.findUnique({ where: { id: userId } });
    const matchingRules = await this.attributeRuleEvaluator.findMatchingRules(user);
    const ruleRoleIds = matchingRules.map((r) => r.role_id);
    const ruleRoles = await this.prisma.roles.findMany({
      where: { id: { in: ruleRoleIds } },
      include: { role_permissions: true },
    });

    // 3. Union
    const allRoles = [...directAssignments.map((ua) => ua.role), ...ruleRoles];
    const permissions = new Set<Permission>();
    for (const role of allRoles) {
      for (const rp of role.role_permissions) {
        permissions.add(rp.permission_key as Permission);
      }
    }
    return permissions;
  }

  async hasPermission(userId: string, required: Permission): Promise<boolean> {
    const permissions = await this.getUserPermissions(userId);
    return permissions.has(required);
  }

  async invalidateUser(userId: string): Promise<void> {
    await this.redis.del(`user_permissions:${userId}`);
  }

  async invalidateRole(roleId: string): Promise<void> {
    // Affected users: direct + rule-matched
    const direct = await this.prisma.user_roles.findMany({
      where: { role_id: roleId },
      select: { user_id: true },
    });
    const ruleMatched = await this.findUsersMatchingRole(roleId);

    const userIds = new Set([
      ...direct.map((d) => d.user_id),
      ...ruleMatched.map((u) => u.id),
    ]);

    if (userIds.size === 0) return;

    const pipeline = this.redis.pipeline();
    for (const uid of userIds) {
      pipeline.del(`user_permissions:${uid}`);
    }
    await pipeline.exec();
  }
}
```

Cache TTL 5 dakika. Invalidation explicit (aşağıdaki trigger'lar).

## Cache Invalidation Triggers

| Event | Action |
|---|---|
| User direct role atanmalı/çıkarılma | `invalidateUser(userId)` |
| Rol'e permission ekleme/kaldırma | `invalidateRole(roleId)` |
| Kullanıcı attribute değişimi (company, department, vs.) | `invalidateUser(userId)` |
| Attribute rule ekleme/güncelleme/silme | `invalidateRole(ruleRoleId)` (etkilenen rol) |
| User deactivate | `invalidateUser(userId)` + session revoke |

NestJS EventEmitter2 kullanılır:

```typescript
// Emit
this.eventEmitter.emit('user.role.changed', { userId, roleId });

// Listen
@OnEvent('user.role.changed')
async handleUserRoleChange(payload) {
  await this.permissionResolver.invalidateUser(payload.userId);
}
```

## Attribute Rule Evaluator

Attribute rule örneği (DB'de):

```json
{
  "id": "rule_123",
  "role_id": "role_USER_MANAGER",
  "condition_groups": [
    {
      "conditions": [
        { "attribute": "companyId", "operator": "equals", "value": "comp_ACME" },
        { "attribute": "departmentId", "operator": "equals", "value": "dep_IT" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "conditions": [
        { "attribute": "positionTitle", "operator": "contains", "value": "Yönetici" }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

Semantics: `(companyId=ACME AND departmentId=IT) OR (positionTitle contains "Yönetici")`. OR between groups, AND within group.

Operator'lar:
- `equals`, `not_equals`
- `contains`, `not_contains` (string)
- `starts_with`, `ends_with`
- `in`, `not_in` (array)
- `greater_than`, `less_than` (date/number)

```typescript
@Injectable()
export class AttributeRuleEvaluatorService {
  evaluateRule(user: User, rule: AttributeRule): boolean {
    return rule.condition_groups.some((group) => 
      group.conditions.every((condition) => this.evaluateCondition(user, condition))
    );
  }

  private evaluateCondition(user: User, condition: Condition): boolean {
    const userValue = this.getAttributeValue(user, condition.attribute);
    switch (condition.operator) {
      case 'equals': return userValue === condition.value;
      case 'contains': return String(userValue).includes(condition.value);
      // ...
    }
  }
}
```

## 4-Katman Enforcement

Her endpoint sırayla 4 kontrol:

### Katman 1: JwtAuthGuard

Token valid + not revoked. `AppModule`'da global guard.

### Katman 2: PermissionGuard + @RequirePermission

Decorator okur, cache'ten permission set alır, required ile kontrol.

```typescript
@Injectable()
export class PermissionGuard implements CanActivate {
  constructor(
    private reflector: Reflector,
    private permissionResolver: PermissionResolverService,
  ) {}

  async canActivate(context: ExecutionContext): Promise<boolean> {
    const required = this.reflector.get<Permission[]>('permissions', context.getHandler());
    if (!required?.length) return true;

    const { user } = context.switchToHttp().getRequest();
    const permissions = await this.permissionResolver.getUserPermissions(user.sub);

    const missing = required.filter((p) => !permissions.has(p));
    if (missing.length > 0) {
      throw new PermissionDeniedException({ required, missing });
    }
    return true;
  }
}
```

### Katman 3: Resource Ownership (Service-Level)

Permission varsa bile kaynak sahipliği check:

```typescript
async findByDisplayId(displayId: string, actor: AuthenticatedUser) {
  const process = await this.prisma.processes.findUnique({
    where: { display_id: displayId },
    include: { tasks: { include: { assignees: true } } },
  });
  if (!process) throw new ProcessNotFoundException();

  const isOwner = process.started_by_user_id === actor.id;
  const isAssignee = process.tasks.some((t) => 
    t.assignees.some((a) => a.user_id === actor.id)
  );
  const hasViewAll = await this.permissionResolver.hasPermission(
    actor.id, 
    Permission.PROCESS_VIEW_ALL,
  );

  if (!isOwner && !isAssignee && !hasViewAll) {
    throw new ProcessAccessDeniedException();
  }

  return this.serialize(process, actor);
}
```

Ownership rules (domain-specific):

| Entity | Kural |
|---|---|
| Process | Starter OR task assignee OR PROCESS_VIEW_ALL |
| Task | Assignee OR parent process starter OR PROCESS_VIEW_ALL |
| Document | Uploader OR parent context erişilebilir OR admin permission |
| User (read) | Self OR USER_LIST_VIEW |
| User (edit) | USER_UPDATE_ATTRIBUTE AND NOT self |
| Notification | Recipient (daima self) |
| Audit log | AUDIT_LOG_VIEW (Superadmin only) |

### Katman 4: Field-Level Filter (Response Serializer)

Entity'yi görme, her field'ını görme değil. Serializer permission-aware:

```typescript
private serialize(process: Process, actor: AuthenticatedUser) {
  const isOwner = process.started_by_user_id === actor.id;
  const hasViewAll = /* check */;
  const isFullAccess = isOwner || hasViewAll;

  return {
    id: process.id,
    displayId: process.display_id,
    status: process.status,
    tasks: process.tasks.map((task) => {
      const isAssignee = task.assignees.some((a) => a.user_id === actor.id);
      const taskFullAccess = isFullAccess || isAssignee;

      return {
        id: task.id,
        stepLabel: task.step_label,
        status: task.status,
        // Full access fields
        formData: taskFullAccess ? task.form_data : null,
        documents: taskFullAccess ? task.documents : [],
        reason: taskFullAccess ? task.reason : null,
      };
    }),
  };
}
```

Field gizlemek = `null` return. Silmek değil. Frontend "Bu bilgi paylaşılmamış" placeholder gösterir.

## @RequirePermission Decorator

```typescript
// apps/api/src/common/decorators/require-permission.decorator.ts
import { SetMetadata } from '@nestjs/common';
import { Permission } from '@leanmgmt/shared-types';

export const RequirePermission = (...permissions: Permission[]) =>
  SetMetadata('permissions', permissions);
```

Usage:
```typescript
@Post('/users')
@RequirePermission(Permission.USER_CREATE)
async create(...) { ... }

@Patch('/roles/:id/permissions')
@RequirePermission(Permission.ROLE_PERMISSION_MANAGE)
async updateRolePermissions(...) { ... }
```

## Banned Patterns

- Permission check'i yalnız frontend'te (backend zorunlu)
- Permission cache'i inline atlama ("bu request için DB'den resolve et")
- Hard-coded permission string (`'USER_CREATE'` — enum kullan)
- Cache invalidation "sonra" bırakma (anında emit)
- Role değişikliğinde manuel cache silme (event pattern'i kullan)
- Field-level filter'ı frontend'te yapma (sensitive data leak)

